Building older jextract versions +> +> The `master` branch always tracks the latest version of the JDK. If you wish to build an older version of jextract, which targets an earlier version of the JDK you can do so by chercking out the appropriate branch. +> For example, to build a jextract tool which works against JDK 18: +> +> `git checkout jdk18` +> +> Over time, new branches will be added, each targeting a specific JDK version. +>
